'''PJKT HorrorCon''' (also written '''Projekt: HorrorCon''' or '''PJKT: HorrorCon''') is a horror-themed community convention in [[Special:MyLanguage/VRChat|VRChat]], organized as a collaboration between [[Community:PJKT|Projekt: Community]] (PJKT) and HorrorConVR.<ref name="legends-wiki">[https://vrchat-legends.fandom.com/wiki/Projekt:_Community "Projekt: Community"] on ''VRChat Legends Wiki''. Retrieved April 9, 2026.</ref> Editions have featured a dedicated convention world, stage programming, improv and storytelling shows, world hops, and guest panels.<ref name="fa-horror-2024-qa">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/59330477/ "HorrorCon 2024 - Your Questions?"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity''. Retrieved July 18, 2026.</ref><ref name="group-fair">[[Community:Group_Fair|Group Fair]] schedule listings for HorrorCon 2025 programming under Projekt Community (PJKT.3741).</ref>

==Overview==

HorrorCon sits on PJKT's autumn calendar. HorrorCon is built around horror communities and entertainment—often in partnership with the HorrorConVR group ('''HORROR.4016''').<ref name="fa-horror-2024-qa"/><ref name="legends-wiki"/>

The Projekt Community website has announced a further run for October 2026.<ref name="pjkt-faq">[https://www.projektcommunity.com/faq "FAQ"] on ''Projekt: Community'' (site banner: "PJKT:HORRORCON IS COMING — October 2026"). Retrieved July 18, 2026.</ref>

==Format==

Documented editions use a themed event world as the convention hub. Programming has included opening and stage sessions, staff Q&A, improv theatre, storytime and spoken-word shows, horror-game voice-actor panels, and collaborative world hops with other groups.<ref name="fa-horror-2024-welcome">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/59329764/ "HorrorCon 2024 - Welcome! Who Wants To Try?"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity''. Retrieved July 18, 2026.</ref><ref name="fa-horror-2024-qa"/><ref name="group-fair"/> Some sessions have been livestreamed or archived on Projekt Community's YouTube channel.<ref name="yt-opening-2025">[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Os-JAVjAPsg "PJKT: HorrorCon 2025 Opening Ceremony"] on ''YouTube'' (@PJKT). Retrieved July 18, 2026.</ref>

==History==

===2024===

PJKT HorrorCon 2024 ran from October 26 to 27, 2024.<ref name="fa-horror-2024-qa"/> The weekend included stage welcomes and improv programming by Skits'N'Bits, as well as a staff Q&A with PJKT and HorrorCon organizers.<ref name="fa-horror-2024-welcome"/><ref name="fa-horror-2024-prompts">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/59329873/ "HorrorCon 2024 - The Prompts"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity''. Retrieved July 18, 2026.</ref><ref name="fa-horror-2024-qa"/> Promotional photography for the edition was staged in the world ''The Ghost Town'' by Coldcancer.<ref name="fa-horror-promo">[https://www.furaffinity.net/view/58916836/ "PJKTCOM HorrorCon 2024 Promo - Terrible Wings"] by ChevronTheWolf on ''Fur Affinity''. Retrieved July 18, 2026.</ref>

===2025===

An opening ceremony was posted to Projekt Community's YouTube channel.<ref name="yt-opening-2025"/> During the overlapping [[Community:Group_Fair|Group Fair]] weekend (October 24-26, 2025), Projekt Community scheduled HorrorCon-branded sessions that included [[Spookality 2025|Spookality]] world hops with Noved Squad, storytime with MrCreepyPasta, SpokenHeart: Spooky Edition, a Faceless ''Dream Crypt'' session, and a horror-game voice-actor Q&A with Autumn Ivy.<ref name="group-fair"/>

===2026===

Projekt Community has announced PJKT HorrorCon for October 2026.<ref name="pjkt-faq"/>

